item.title: Ljubicic wins second title of 2006
item.description: Top-seeded Ivan Ljubicic defeated Austrian qualifier Stefan Koubek 6-3 6-4 to clinch his second title of the year at the Zagreb Indoors on Sunday.

item.title: Gonzales will face grilling on spy program
item.description: U.S. Attorney General Alberto Gonzales is poised to defend President Bush's controversial domestic spying program Monday when he testifies at a Senate Judiciary Committee hearing on the program.

item.title: Cartoon protesters burn consulate
item.description: Thousands of protesters packed the streets of Beirut, Lebanon, on Sunday, some clashing with security forces and setting the Danish Consulate on fire in anger over cartoons depicting the Prophet Mohammed.

item.title: Roadside bomb kills 2 in Baghdad
item.description: A roadside bomb targeting an Iraqi police patrol detonated Sunday afternoon in southeast Baghdad, killing two civilians and wounding five others and two police officers, Baghdad police told CNN.

item.title: Chelsea complete Liverpool double
item.description: Chelsea tightened their vice-like grip on the English title race with a 2-0 home win over European champions Liverpool to re-open their 15-point advantage on Sunday.

item.title: Woods defeats Els in Dubai playoff
item.description: Tiger Woods continued his perfect start to 2006 with a playoff victory over defending champion Ernie Els in the Dubai Desert Classic on Sunday.

item.title: USS Cole plotter escapes prison
